item.description:
dwmblocks is a modular status bar written in c . It is used with dwm to display status bar information.
The status bar is at the top right corner. It shows information like current date, time, weather, network IO, RAM usage and volume. That information gets updated based on predefined rules in your configuration file, which might look something like this:
//Modify this file to change what commands output to your statusbar, and recompile using the make command.
